  "slug": "crepes",
  "title": "Crepes",
  "subtitle": null,
  "excerpt": "Crepes. A home-cook's recipe from Rebecca's collection, kept in the family rotation.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Crepes. Classical French method, scaled to a home kitchen. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A weeknight-friendly recipe: most of the work is the prep, and the cooking takes care of itself.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Plain flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 250,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2xb0000rkv47vd545ba",
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": null,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            },
            {
              "name": "Caster sugar",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "for sweet pancakes, if you're adding sweet toppings it's not really essential",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fau900dvrkv4ce3mot41",
              "ingredientSlug": "caster-sugar"
            },
            {
              "name": "Eggs",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 3,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3wj001prkv40f7svjvg",
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs"
            },
            {
              "name": "Vegetable oil",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fant00dlrkv4gy5hjxkm",
              "ingredientSlug": "vegetable-oil"
            },
            {
              "name": "Whole milk",
              "unit": "ml",
              "amount": 500,
              "prepNote": "or vegan alternative",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3be000nrkv4co43fp6z",
              "ingredientSlug": "whole-milk"
            },
            {
              "name": "Salted butter",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": null,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3h0000xrkv4pb5h36z0",
              "ingredientSlug": "salted-butter"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To make by hand, place the flour and pinch of salt in a large mixing bowl and make a well in the centre.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat the eggs and oil in a measuring jug. Pour into the well you made. Pour the milk into the measuring jug and pour half of the milk into the bowl with the other ingredients. Using a whisk, mix everything together, drawing the flour into the wet ingredients until the mixture is smooth and lump free. Pour in the remaining milk, whisking constantly, until you have a smooth, lump free, thin batter. It should be the consistency of single (pouring) cream.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Alternatively, blend all the ingredients in a blender, switching the power off the second the mixture is smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Allow the batter to rest for a minimum of 30 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Place a large non-stick frying pan over a medium heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Place a small knob of butter in the pan and wipe the excess off with a paper towel.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Using a ladle, pour some pancake batter and tilt the pan slightly to spread the batter all over the base of the pan.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook for 2-3 minutes or until the bottom of the pancake is golden brown, then toss or turn over with a spatula.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The first pancake is always the worst one - so don't think you are doing something wrong! It will still taste good so this is the cook's treat! The next will be better, I promise.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Repeat the process above until all of the batter is used up.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Topping Ideas",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Fill the pancakes with whipped cream, drizzle with sticky toffee sauce and sprinkle with chopped nuts.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Mix until just combined; lumps are fine. Rest the batter 10 minutes before cooking.",
              "cause": "Over-mixed batter, gluten developed.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes are tough or chewy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use fresh raising agents and melted butter, not cold. Don't flatten when flipping.",
              "cause": "Baking powder stale, or butter too cool.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes are flat, not fluffy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Medium heat, butter or oil swirled before each pancake. Wait until bubbles appear on top before flipping.",
              "cause": "Pan not hot enough, or not enough fat.",
              "symptom": "Stuck to the pan"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat. Cook longer per side at lower temperature for a more even brown.",
              "cause": "Pan too hot.",
              "symptom": "Cooked unevenly, pale in the middle, dark at the edges"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sweet: serve with maple syrup, lemon and sugar, or fresh berries and yoghurt.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Savoury: skip the sugar in the batter; top with smoked salmon, cream cheese, and chives.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Crepes are French in origin. They come from Brittany, where buckwheat galettes (the savoury version) and wheat crepes (the sweet) have been made for centuries. The thin batter and quick-cook method is the same across both. Writers like Elizabeth David and Julia Child brought the technique into the English-speaking kitchen from the 1950s onward.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
